answers.body_markdown:
If the item is a checkbox based on a list of values, the user might choose multiple values, so you need to cater for this possibility. The values will be separated by colons (:), e.g. `Admin:Reader`.

For example:

    IF instr(&#39;:&#39; || :P30_ROLE_ID || &#39;:&#39;, &#39;:Admin:&#39;) &gt; 0 THEN
       :P30_NAME :=  &#39;30&#39;;
    elsif instr(&#39;:&#39; || :P30_ROLE_ID || &#39;:&#39;, &#39;:Reader:&#39;) &gt; 0 then
       :P30_NAME :=  &#39;20&#39;; 
    elsif instr(&#39;:&#39; || :P30_ROLE_ID || &#39;:&#39;, &#39;:User:&#39;) &gt; 0 then
       :P30_NAME :=  &#39;10&#39;; 
    END IF;

